# project convention
## Update Version
When asked to update to a new version, you should Do the following
1. Increase the version in @VERSION
2. Summarize current changes and add it into change log in @docs/CHANGELOG.md
3. Update todo list in @docs/todo.md
4. If it a new feature, add a paragraph in the README.md. If it is changes to bug fix. Correction the description in README.md if needed. If new docs created., cite it in README.md which is the entry point of the project
5. git commit the changes
6. git push to remote
7. git create merge request